OL,6,F"There is no intrinsic reason why
OL,7,Fteaching should have such high levels
OL,8,Fof burnout. Things can and should be
OL,9,Fdifferent and we need the next
OL,10,Fgovernment to work with us to restore
OL,11,Fteaching to a profession where
OL,12,Fteachers can thrive, not just struggle
OL,13,Fto survive."
OL,15,FA Department for Education (DfE)
OL,16,Fspokesperson said: "We recognise the
OL,17,Fextraordinary work that headteachers,
OL,18,Fteachers and other staff in schools
OL,19,Fprovide, and we take their wellbeing
OL,20,Fvery seriously.
